==English==

===Etymology===
From Spanish ''[[huracán]]'', ultimately from the name of a [[Carib]] god of storm in Taino language.

===Pronunciation===
*(''[[RP]]''): hŭ'rĭ-kən, /{{IPAchar|ˈhʌrɪkən}}/, /<tt>"hVrIk@n</tt>/<!--note: there no secondary stress in this word in RP-->
*(''US''): hŭr'ĭ-kān" ''or'' hŭr'ə-kān", /ˈhʌrɪˌkeɪn/ ''or'' /ˈhʌrəˌkeɪn/, /<tt>"hVrI%keIn</tt>/ ''or'' /<tt>"hVr@%keIn</tt>/

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''hurricane''' (''plural'' '''hurricanes''')

#An Atlantic and north-eastern Pacific [[weather]] [[phenomenon]] that originates in the [[tropics]] and has sustained [[wind]] speeds equal to or greater than 74 mph (120 km/h)

